'''Ceremonial marriage''' is a common form of [[marriage]] in which a couple follows laws and procedures specified by the state in order to gain recognition of their marriage (ex. buying a [[marriage license]], participating in a ceremony led by an authorized official, having witnesses at a ceremony). They are often accompanied by [[wedding]]s, and have different forms, reflecting particular religious and philosophical views of the couple.

Ceremonial marriage is an opposite to [[common-law marriage]].

